  "title": "Process Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong> </strong><u><strong>Duties and Responsibilities</strong></u><br />- Planned and maintaining process routing in ERP system\nwhenever there is a new work order launched.</p><p>- Coordinate with CNC Programming team on all NPI & FA\nfabrication.</p><p>- Identify opportunities for fabrication process improvement\nfor existing high-runner and repeated jobs.</p><p>- Supporting the Quality MRB meeting and advice disposition\naccordingly.</p><p>- Prepare PMP/FMEA and work instruction for FA submission.</p><p>- Perform new products' manufacturing studies and develop\nprocess control specifications.</p><p>- Review process specifications to be in line with changes in\nproduct specs, process, and quality improvement.</p><p>- Strong decision-making and troubleshooting skills\nand methods are essential<br /></p><p><u><strong>Requirement</strong></u><br />- Min. Diploma/Degree in Mechanical, Engineering-related courses or any\nequivalent.</p><p>- Min 2-3 years of metal fabrication or precision engineering experience.<br />- Detail oriented.</p><p>- Good verbal and written communication skills.</p><p>- Self-motivated to work independently with team support & minimal guidance.</p><p>- Ability to maintain a positive attitude at all times.</p><p>-Computer knowledge with MS Office, etc.</p>",
